    <h1>Summary of Discord Terms of Service</h1>

    <h2>1. Who Can Use Discord</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You must be at least 13 years old (or older, depending on your country).</li>
        <li>If you're a minor, your parent or guardian also agrees to the Terms and is responsible for your use.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. What Discord Provides</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Voice, video, and text chat via servers and direct messages.</li>
        <li>Features may be added, removed, or changed over time.</li>
        <li>Integrations with other apps (e.g., games, music) for activity display and sharing.</li>
        <li>Personalized recommendations based on your activity and settings.</li>
        <li>Safety tools like Family Center for guardian monitoring (without access to private messages).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Your Account</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You must keep your account secure (password, 2FA).</li>
        <li>You must provide accurate information and update it when necessary.</li>
        <li>You cannot sell, transfer, or lend your account or username.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Content & Licensing</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You own the content you post.</li>
        <li>By posting, you grant Discord a worldwide, royalty-free license to use your content to operate the service.</li>
        <li>Discord may remove content that violates rules or laws.</li>
        <li>Discord owns its own branding, design, and platform content.</li>
        <li>Discord is not responsible for accuracy or behavior related to other users’ content.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Software Use</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You receive a limited license to install and use the Discord app.</li>
        <li>You may not reverse-engineer, decompile, or redistribute their software.</li>
        <li>Some portions are open-source with separate licensing terms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. What You Can’t Do</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>No illegal activity, harassment, hacking, or spam.</li>
        <li>No scraping, data harvesting, or overloading the platform.</li>
        <li>You must follow laws, Community Guidelines, and all platform rules.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Termination of Use</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You can delete your account at any time.</li>
        <li>Discord may suspend or terminate your account for violations, legal reasons, risk, or inactivity.</li>
        <li>Certain terms continue to apply after termination (e.g., content license, indemnity).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. Appeals</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You may appeal account or content moderation decisions.</li>
        <li>EU users must appeal within six months of the decision.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9. Liability & Warranties</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Discord is provided “as is” with no guaranteed uptime or performance.</li>
        <li>You are responsible for data charges from your ISP or mobile provider.</li>
        <li>Discord’s liability is limited (often capped at what you paid in 3 months or $100).</li>
        <li>Discord is not responsible for other users’ behavior or content.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>10. Legal Disputes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Most disputes (especially in the U.S. and Canada) must be resolved through arbitration.</li>
        <li>There is a class-action waiver.</li>
        <li>In some cases, you can opt out of arbitration.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>11. Indemnity</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You agree to cover Discord’s costs if your actions or content cause legal issues.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>12. Updates to the Terms</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Discord may update its Terms of Service.</li>
        <li>Material changes will have reasonable advance notice (unless urgent).</li>
        <li>Continued use after updates means you accept the new terms.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>13. Additional Legal Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>You must comply with export control laws.</li>
        <li>If any part of the Terms is invalid, the remaining sections still apply.</li>
        <li>Discord may transfer its rights; you generally cannot.</li>
        <li>Some clauses persist even after service use ends.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>14. Entire Agreement</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>The Terms, Privacy Policy, and other rules form the full agreement.</li>
        <li>Specific feature terms override general TOS where necessary.</li>
    </ul>

